{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Modeling a Helical-Cruciform Fuel Rod Assembly"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This notebook is intended to demonstrate how to use ROBIN3's [Python API](../pythonapi/index.rst) to simulate a helical-cruciform fuel rod assembly. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "import math\n",
    "from pprint import pprint\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import robin3\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = [12, 6]\n",
    "robin3.config.USE_TQDM_NOTEBOOK = True"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Defining Materials"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here we define a [material] (../io_formats/input.rst#material-object) list containing a 4.5% enriched UO2 material as follows:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "uo2 = {\n",
    "    \"name\": \"FUEL\",\n",
    "    \"elements\": [\"UO2_4.5\"],\n",
    "    \"weight_percents\": [1.0],\n",
    "    \"density\": 10.0\n",
    "}\n",
    "materials = [uo2]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Defining Pin Structures"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First we create a guide tube [structure](../io_formats/input.rst#structure-object)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "guide_tube = {\n",
    "    \"name\": \"GT\",\n",
    "    \"primitives\": [\n",
    "        {\"type\": \"CIRCLE\", \"radius\": 0.5615},\n",
    "        {\"type\": \"CIRCLE\", \"radius\": 0.6120},\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    \"regions\": [\n",
    "        {\"material\": \"ZIRC4\", \"space\": \"2-1\"},\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note here we do not define the region inside the guide tube, ROBIN3 will automactically \"fill\" the undefined regions with moderator. Material \"ZIR4\" are pre-defined in ROBIN3's [material databank file](../io_formats/materialdb.rst), which can be inspected by [robin3.get_predefined_materials](../pythonapi/generated/robin3.get_predefined_materials.rst) as well."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Second we define some functions in order to generate helical-cruciform fuel rod [structure](../io_formats/input.rst#structure-object) at different twist angle conveniently."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def rotate(angle, point):\n",
    "    PI = 3.1425926\n",
    "    angle = angle / 180 * PI\n",
    "    x, y = point\n",
    "    _x = math.cos(angle) * x - math.sin(angle) * y\n",
    "    _y = math.sin(angle) * x + math.cos(angle) * y\n",
    "    return _x, _y\n",
    "\n",
    "def circle(radius, center):\n",
    "    x, y = center\n",
    "    return {\"type\": \"CIRCLE\", \n",
    "            \"radius\": radius,\n",
    "            \"center\": {\"x\": x, \"y\": y}}\n",
    "\n",
    "def helical_cruciform_rod(name, rotate_angle, scale, num_rings):\n",
    "    r1, r2, r3, r4, r5 = np.array(\n",
    "        [0.1046, 0.1147, 0.1859, 0.3475, 0.5334]) * scale\n",
    "    centers_in = [rotate(rotate_angle, p) for p in [(-1, 0), (0, -1), (1, 0), (0, 1)]]\n",
    "    centers_in = np.array(centers_in) * r5\n",
    "    centers_out = [rotate(rotate_angle, p) for p in [(-1, -1), (1, -1), (1, 1), (-1, 1)]]\n",
    "    centers_out = np.array(centers_out) * r5\n",
    "    primitives = [{\"type\": \"POLYGON\",\n",
    "           \"vertexes\": [{\"x\": x, \"y\": y} for x, y in centers_out]}]\n",
    "    regions, start, container_inner = [], 2, ''\n",
    "    for radius, material in zip([r1, r2, r3], [\"FUEL\", \"HE\", \"ZIRC4\"]):\n",
    "        for p in centers_in:\n",
    "            primitives.append(circle(radius, p))\n",
    "        for p in centers_out:\n",
    "            primitives.append(circle(r4+r3-radius, p))\n",
    "        container = \"{}|{}|{}|{}|(1-{}-{}-{}-{})\".format(*np.arange(start, start+8))\n",
    "        space = container if not container_inner else \"({})-({})\".format(container, container_inner)\n",
    "        regions.append({\"material\": material, \"space\": space})\n",
    "#         break\n",
    "        container_inner = container\n",
    "        start += 8\n",
    "    meshing = {\n",
    "        \"type\": \"SECTORS\",\n",
    "        \"num_azimuths\": 8,\n",
    "        \"radii\": [0.2, 0.35, r5+r3]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    return {\"name\": name, \"meshing\": meshing, \"primitives\": primitives, \"regions\": regions}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We use function defined above to create helical-cruciform fuel rod [structure](../io_formats/input.rst#structure-object) at a squence of twist angles: [0, 15, 30, 45, 60, 75]."
   ]
  },

    "## Defining Assemblies"
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here we define a list of 17x17 square [Assembly](../io_formats/input.rst#assembly-object) at different twist angles. That means we treat different twist angle assemblies as different kind of assemblies."
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def assembly(name, angle):\n",
    "    rod = \"HC{}\".format(int(angle))\n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        \"name\": \"hc_assembly_{}_degrees_twisted\".format(int(angle)),\n",
    "        \"type\": \"SQUARE\",\n",
    "        \"symmetry\": 8,\n",
    "        \"pitch\": 21.504,\n",
    "        \"cell_pitch\": 1.26,\n",
    "        \"cell_map\": [\n",
    "            rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod,\"GT\", rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod,\n",
    "            rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod, rod\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "assembly_names = [\"hc_assembly_{}_degrees_twisted\".format(int(angle)) for angle in rotate_angles]\n",
    "assemblies = [assembly(n, a) for n, a in zip(assembly_names, rotate_angles)]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Defining State Points"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "[State points](../io_formats/input.rst#state-points-object) is required for micro xs cases, here we provides [burnup points](../io_formats/input.rst#burnup-points) and [power density](../io_formats/input.rst#power-density) to perform single assembly depletion calculation:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "state_points = {\n",
    "    \"boron_concentration\": 500,\n",
    "    \"moderator_temperature\": 577,\n",
    "    \"fuel_temperature\": 903,\n",
    "    \"system_pressure\": 15.51\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Composing Input Model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The full [input model](../io_formats/input.rst) for a typical single assembly depletion calculation includes following parts:\n",
    "    1. [materials](../io_formats/input.rst#materials-array);\n",
    "    2. [structures](../io_formats/input.rst#structures-array);\n",
    "    3. [assemblies](../io_formats/input.rst#assemblies-array);\n",
    "    4. [state points](../io_formats/input.rst#state-points-object)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here we define a list of models, each model represent a certain twisted assembly:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 34,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "models = [{\n",
    "    \"materials\": materials,\n",
    "    \"structures\": structures,\n",
    "    \"assemblies\": [assembly],\n",
    "    \"state_points\": state_points\n",
    "} for assembly in assemblies]\n",
    "# import json\n",
    "# with open('hc_assembly.json', 'w') as f:\n",
    "#     json.dump(model[0], f)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Visualizing Input Model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Instantiates a list of [robin3.plotter](../pythonapi/generated/robin3.Plotter.rst) to visualize assemblies at different twist angles with fine meshes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 35,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plotters = [robin3.Plotter(model) for model in models]"

    "## Run ROBIN3"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Running ROBIN3 from Python can be done using the [robin3.run()](../pythonapi/generated/robin3.run.rst) function. This function allows you to use GPU by setting use_GPU=True if it needed, GPU will significantly reduce the running time."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 38,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "results = [robin3.run(model, use_gpu=True) for model in models]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 39,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[<robin3.result_process.ResultProcessor object at 0x7fab64472668>, <robin3.result_process.ResultProcessor object at 0x7fab646b32b0>, <robin3.result_process.ResultProcessor object at 0x7fab942512e8>, <robin3.result_process.ResultProcessor object at 0x7fab843d6cf8>, <robin3.result_process.ResultProcessor object at 0x7fab336e7048>, <robin3.result_process.ResultProcessor object at 0x7fab843d6828>]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(results)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The [robin3.run()](../pythonapi/generated/robin3.run.rst) function return a [robin3.ResultProcessor](../pythonapi/generated/robin3.ResultProcessor.rst) instance. Here we get a list of [robin3.ResultProcessor](../pythonapi/generated/robin3.ResultProcessor.rst) instance for each twisted assembly. All the result data can be accessed by the result_data attribute, and the result data are saved by a HDF5 file named by\n",
    "result_file attribute, summary result data such as keff can be inspected by method summary which return a pandas DataFrame."
   ]
  },
